      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Digital eye strain and allergies can indeed cause redness and discomfort, but self-diagnosing and treating without professional advice can be risky. Antihistamines might help with allergy symptoms, but they won't address potential infections or other serious conditions. It's always best to err on the side of caution with your health. If you're unable to see a doctor immediately, consider at least reducing screen time, taking frequent breaks, and ensuring proper lighting to minimize strain. And remember, if symptoms worsen or new ones appear, seek medical attention sooner rather than later. Your eyes are crucial for your daily functioning, and it's better to be safe than sorry.",
